metadata.name: Woman in Red
metadata.description:
"I like your camera!" she shouted, as I obliviously walked by her. 

I had been around the block a few times by this point, and when I approached the woman with a smile, she looked at me, but seemed more focused on the camera as her eyes lit up with curiosity. 

Her english was broken, but I could tell she wanted to look at the camera, and I happily obliged. We exchanged a few words as she admired it, and we went on our way.

A smile was on her face for the entirety of the exchange. She went to leave, all the while whistling a tune as she turned a corner.
